HEADWORD: Ghibelline
<hw>Ghib"el*line</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It.
<ets>Ghibellino</ets>; of German origin.]</ety> <fld>(It. Hist.)</fld>
<def>One of a faction in Italy, in the 12th and 13th centuries, which
favored the German emperors, and opposed the Guelfs, or adherents of the
poses.</def> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

